{
  "texts": [
    "7.3 Core Limitations of AI in QA Despite its advantages, AI in QA presents several barriers that must be carefully considered: 1.",
    "High Dependency on Quality Training Data AI models are only as good as the data they are trained on.",
    "Inconsistent, biased, or insufficient datasets can degrade model performance, leading to incorrect test prioritization or irrelevant test cases. 2.",
    "Explainability and Interpretability Issues AI decisions-particularly those made by black-box models like deep neural networks-can be difficult to interpret.",
    "This poses a problem in highly regulated industries (e.g., healthcare, finance), where traceability and auditability are mandatory. 3."
  ]
}